refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;
stringfalseMemcache::findserver stringkey
Memcache::findserver determines, from the servers in the connection pool, which one would handle the given key according to the pool's hashing strategy. This makes it possible to know where an item is (or would be) stored without actually reading or writing it.

&reftitle.parameters;


  key


    The key for which the responsible server is looked up.

  &reftitle.examples;



    Memcache::findserver example


<?php

$memcache_obj = new Memcache;

/* add two servers to the pool */
$memcache_obj->addServer('memcache_host1', 11211);
$memcache_obj->addServer('memcache_host2', 11211);

/* find out which server would handle 'var_key' */
$server = $memcache_obj->findserver('var_key');

echo $server;

?>


    &example.outputs.similar;


memcache_host1:11211
